WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.650 --> 00:00:02.439
Previously on Siren...

2
00:00:02.440 --> 00:00:03.689
This will end
very badly.

3
00:00:03.690 --> 00:00:05.569
You need
to find her sister.

4
00:00:05.570 --> 00:00:06.400
Close the glass!

5
00:00:09.940 --> 00:00:11.860
Come on. let's get
out of here. okay?

6
00:00:13.690 --> 00:00:16.729
This part tells us
where you are.

7
00:00:16.730 --> 00:00:17.730
I come back.

8
00:00:17.731 --> 00:00:19.149
Donna?

9
00:00:19.150 --> 00:00:20.479
Hey. are you all right?

10
00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:22.439
I think you might be
in shock.

11
00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:23.479
Hey. it's me.

12
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:24.939
Chris?!

13
00:00:24.940 --> 00:00:26.019
Chris. you're alive?!

14
00:00:26.020 --> 00:00:27.020
Chris!

15
00:00:27.021 --> 00:00:28.649
He needs help. man.

16
00:00:30.150 --> 00:00:31.900
She found her sister.

17
00:00:33.690 --> 00:00:36.729
Home. We lost her.

18
00:00:36.730 --> 00:00:38.279
That's the place
where they held Chris.

19
00:00:38.280 --> 00:00:40.479
They're wiping out
all of the evidence.

20
00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:41.480
They'll be coming for him.

21
00:00:55.650 --> 00:00:57.019
They taste better cold.

22
00:00:57.020 --> 00:00:58.440
On the house.

23
00:01:00.780 --> 00:01:02.570
Thanks.

24
00:01:18.820 --> 00:01:21.520
You're
a hard man to track down.

25
00:01:24.110 --> 00:01:26.860
Glad to see you
looking so healthy.

26
00:01:31.780 --> 00:01:32.980
You remember me?

27
00:01:35.070 --> 00:01:37.650
I saw you at that...
place.

28
00:01:39.520 --> 00:01:41.899
What do you want?

29
00:01:41.900 --> 00:01:44.729
We found that nurse's car
out by Libbey Beach.

30
00:01:44.730 --> 00:01:47.569
When we didn't find you.
we were concerned.

31
00:01:47.570 --> 00:01:51.189
because the woman
you left with.
that nurse. she's...

32
00:01:51.190 --> 00:01:53.319
A nut job?

33
00:01:53.320 --> 00:01:54.570
Unstable.

34
00:01:57.690 --> 00:01:59.980
She's killed several people.

35
00:02:01.440 --> 00:02:03.479
Yeah?

36
00:02:03.480 --> 00:02:06.189
She is extremely violent.

37
00:02:06.190 --> 00:02:08.649
Now. do you know
where she is?

38
00:02:08.650 --> 00:02:10.649
No.

39
00:02:10.650 --> 00:02:14.439
She bolted
as soon as we got
to the beach. okay?

40
00:02:14.440 --> 00:02:16.729
I haven't seen her since.

41
00:02:16.730 --> 00:02:19.479
Glad to hear it.

42
00:02:19.480 --> 00:02:20.609
Yeah.

43
00:02:20.610 --> 00:02:22.609
But if you don't mind.

44
00:02:22.610 --> 00:02:24.649
I want you to tell me

45
00:02:24.650 --> 00:02:26.900
everything
you know about her.

46
00:02:28.860 --> 00:02:32.730
♪ Let the wall break down ♪

47
00:02:48.150 --> 00:02:49.779
Hey.

48
00:02:49.780 --> 00:02:51.479
You want to tell me
where you've been?

49
00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:54.859
Hey. I took the boat out
early this morning.

50
00:02:54.860 --> 00:02:56.779
Really? 'Cause I was here
super early.

51
00:02:56.780 --> 00:02:58.609
and there was no boat
and no you.

52
00:02:58.610 --> 00:03:00.279
Okay. Last night.

53
00:03:00.280 --> 00:03:03.110
Female Dragon Fish.

54
00:03:04.070 --> 00:03:05.649
Deep sea species. right?

55
00:03:05.650 --> 00:03:07.519
Lives 2.000 feet down.

56
00:03:07.520 --> 00:03:10.229
so how'd it wind up
floating dead at the surface?

57
00:03:10.230 --> 00:03:12.649
It must have died
near the top.

58
00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:14.109
Where'd you find it?

59
00:03:14.110 --> 00:03:15.939
Out past the Northern Break.

60
00:03:15.940 --> 00:03:17.279
Let me guess.
At the coordinates

61
00:03:17.280 --> 00:03:18.819
where Ryn's tracker dropped out?

62
00:03:18.820 --> 00:03:20.149
Yeah. you know the place.

63
00:03:20.150 --> 00:03:21.729
We've been there
a thousand times.

64
00:03:21.730 --> 00:03:23.109
Yeah. but not alone

65
00:03:23.110 --> 00:03:25.149
and not in the middle
of the night.

66
00:03:25.150 --> 00:03:26.819
It's kind of extreme. dude.

67
00:03:26.820 --> 00:03:28.689
Kind of stupid.

68
00:03:28.690 --> 00:03:31.689
I just want to know if things
are okay where she is.

69
00:03:31.690 --> 00:03:33.729
It's been a month.

70
00:03:33.730 --> 00:03:34.899
She could be anywhere
by now.

71
00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:36.860
Plus. I...

72
00:03:39.190 --> 00:03:41.069
What?

73
00:03:41.070 --> 00:03:43.819
I miss you.

74
00:03:43.820 --> 00:03:46.109
We had this huge thing
happen to us.

75
00:03:46.110 --> 00:03:47.859
and I feel like
we should be closer.

76
00:03:47.860 --> 00:03:51.359
but it feels like
you're not here.

77
00:03:51.360 --> 00:03:53.939
I am. all right?
I'm right here.

78
00:03:53.940 --> 00:03:56.019
Are you?

79
00:03:56.020 --> 00:03:59.519
Yes. I am.

80
00:03:59.520 --> 00:04:01.110
I'm here.

81
00:04:05.610 --> 00:04:07.519
Well. darlin'.
I'll send in these labs.

82
00:04:07.520 --> 00:04:08.939
and we should get
a yea or nay

83
00:04:08.940 --> 00:04:10.939
on that medical trial
in the next day or so.

84
00:04:10.940 --> 00:04:12.320
Fingers crossed?

85
00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:19.319
By the by.
I. ran into Ben.

86
00:04:19.320 --> 00:04:21.689
Then you've seen him
more than I have
in the last month.

87
00:04:21.690 --> 00:04:23.729
How did he look?

88
00:04:23.730 --> 00:04:26.519
Whole thing seemed a bit off
to tell you the truth.

89
00:04:26.520 --> 00:04:27.939
Kelly Osterman's
water broke.

90
00:04:27.940 --> 00:04:29.609
so I ended up heading out
to go see them

91
00:04:29.610 --> 00:04:30.979
on-board
their four sleeper.

92
00:04:30.980 --> 00:04:32.399
On the way back in.

93
00:04:32.400 --> 00:04:33.979
I passed Ben heading
out in his trawler.

94
00:04:33.980 --> 00:04:36.189
What was off about that?

95
00:04:36.190 --> 00:04:38.229
Well. it was 3 AM.

96
00:04:39.820 --> 00:04:41.939
Was he alone?

97
00:04:41.940 --> 00:04:43.569
Yeah. I'm pretty sure he was.

98
00:04:43.570 --> 00:04:46.149
He wasn't with. you know.
Dale Bishop's girl?

99
00:04:46.150 --> 00:04:48.109
No. Maddie wasn't there.

100
00:04:48.110 --> 00:04:49.979
Thought maybe they were
on the outs actually.

101
00:04:49.980 --> 00:04:52.069
Not that I'm aware of.

102
00:04:52.070 --> 00:04:53.779
What would make you
think that?

103
00:04:53.780 --> 00:04:56.149
About a month ago.
Ben called me twice

104
00:04:56.150 --> 00:04:57.689
to check on
this damsel in distress

105
00:04:57.690 --> 00:04:59.479
he picked up
by the side of the road.

106
00:04:59.480 --> 00:05:01.279
The girl was never there
when I showed up.

107
00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:03.569
either time.

108
00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:06.479
And the second time.
Ben was out cold
on the docks.

109
00:05:06.480 --> 00:05:08.439
I don't know.
Seems to me

110
00:05:08.440 --> 00:05:11.020
the kind of thing
people might break up over.

111
00:05:13.480 --> 00:05:15.899
That's just my boy.

112
00:05:15.900 --> 00:05:18.859
He's always on a mission
to save some...

113
00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:20.280
sad thing.

114
00:05:21.570 --> 00:05:22.819
Anyways.
thank you for that.

115
00:05:22.820 --> 00:05:24.979
Please don't tell him
that I...

116
00:05:24.980 --> 00:05:27.279
Winston. why would I
rat you out?

117
00:05:27.280 --> 00:05:30.070
You're how I know
what my son's up to.

118
00:05:37.860 --> 00:05:39.819
How about we go out.

119
00:05:39.820 --> 00:05:41.569
you know.
like regular people.

120
00:05:41.570 --> 00:05:43.019
take you to dinner?

121
00:05:43.020 --> 00:05:45.939
We can get drunk.
have clumsy sex.

122
00:05:45.940 --> 00:05:47.859
Like regular people?

123
00:05:47.860 --> 00:05:49.569
Yeah.
regular clumsy people.

124
00:05:53.020 --> 00:05:54.779
Guys!!

125
00:05:54.780 --> 00:05:57.069
Okay.
It's cool. Sorry.

126
00:05:57.070 --> 00:05:59.439
Keep goin' with that.

127
00:05:59.440 --> 00:06:04.939
There was a nasty accident
on the fishing lanes.

128
00:06:04.940 --> 00:06:06.480
It was a local boat.

129
00:06:14.780 --> 00:06:17.069
Guy's lucky the line
didn't slice off his arm.

130
00:06:17.070 --> 00:06:18.859
How'd it happen?

131
00:06:18.860 --> 00:06:20.779
Last month. '
we've been fishin'
our asses off.

132
00:06:20.780 --> 00:06:23.019
crews are tired.
guys are gettin' hurt.

133
00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:25.189
The money's great.
but we can't keep this up.

134
00:06:25.190 --> 00:06:26.439
Somebody's gonna die.

135
00:06:26.440 --> 00:06:28.229
You gotta slow down. man.

136
00:06:28.230 --> 00:06:31.019
I mean.
what about the fishing
and game regulations?

137
00:06:31.020 --> 00:06:32.069
Quotas?

138
00:06:32.070 --> 00:06:33.479
I don't know about that.

139
00:06:33.480 --> 00:06:34.979
but right now. they got us
pullin' everything.

140
00:06:34.980 --> 00:06:36.899
Young. old. sick. weird.

141
00:06:36.900 --> 00:06:38.479
No one seems to care.

142
00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:41.109
I care. You care.

143
00:06:41.110 --> 00:06:42.979
And I know you guys
are just trying
to make a living.

144
00:06:42.980 --> 00:06:45.069
but people
are getting hurt. Xan.

145
00:06:45.070 --> 00:06:46.899
It's not worth it.

146
00:06:46.900 --> 00:06:48.900
- Let's do something
about it.

147
00:06:50.900 --> 00:06:54.689
All right.
All right. I'm done.

148
00:06:54.690 --> 00:06:56.899
All right. find out
what you can from your dad

149
00:06:56.900 --> 00:06:59.109
and the guys on the lanes
and see who's
allowing all this.

150
00:06:59.110 --> 00:07:01.149
I'll figure out what's
happening on the fishery side.

151
00:07:01.150 --> 00:07:03.279
what we're doing
with all this junk fish.

152
00:07:03.280 --> 00:07:05.899
Hey. you mind
if we take this?

153
00:07:05.900 --> 00:07:07.319
Yeah. sure.
It's not good eatin'.

154
00:07:07.320 --> 00:07:08.979
but.
yeah. have at it.

155
00:07:08.980 --> 00:07:10.320
- Have fun.
- Thanks.

156
00:07:14.610 --> 00:07:16.730
Pownall Seafood.

157
00:07:18.440 --> 00:07:20.229
They told me you were here.

158
00:07:20.230 --> 00:07:21.439
Thanks. Bertie.

159
00:07:21.440 --> 00:07:22.649
Thought I was dreaming.

160
00:07:22.650 --> 00:07:23.939
Ha ha.

161
00:07:23.940 --> 00:07:25.729
Been a little while.
hasn't it?

162
00:07:25.730 --> 00:07:27.189
Yeah. I'm sorry.

163
00:07:27.190 --> 00:07:29.399
It's been busy
at the Center.

164
00:07:29.400 --> 00:07:31.819
I'd like to think
you're here to say hi
to your own dad.

165
00:07:31.820 --> 00:07:34.319
but I think I know
better than that
by now. don't I?

166
00:07:34.320 --> 00:07:36.149
What's up. kiddo?

167
00:07:36.150 --> 00:07:39.359
Doug told me you were
thinking about bringing me on.

168
00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:40.939
environmental consultant?

169
00:07:40.940 --> 00:07:42.689
I didn't know
he said anything.

170
00:07:42.690 --> 00:07:44.819
Listen. I know
it's not your bag.

171
00:07:44.820 --> 00:07:47.189
but just. before
you make a decision.
just hear me out.

172
00:07:47.190 --> 00:07:48.190
Let's do it.

173
00:07:48.191 --> 00:07:50.149
Really?

174
00:07:50.150 --> 00:07:51.609
You serious?
You're not screwin'
with me?

175
00:07:51.610 --> 00:07:53.979
No. I'm in.

176
00:07:57.020 --> 00:07:59.189
You don't know.
This is...

177
00:07:59.190 --> 00:08:00.439
This is a big deal to me.

178
00:08:00.440 --> 00:08:03.439
I want to help you
find a better way to fish.

179
00:08:03.440 --> 00:08:06.189
Maybe even make you guys
some more money.

180
00:08:06.190 --> 00:08:07.399
I think we're fishing
just fine.

181
00:08:07.400 --> 00:08:08.899
but if you think
you've got a way

182
00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:10.819
to make me more money.
I'm all ears.

183
00:08:10.820 --> 00:08:12.689
All right.
why don't you come by
tomorrow morning?

184
00:08:12.690 --> 00:08:14.109
See how we do things.

185
00:08:14.110 --> 00:08:15.819
and then we can talk.

186
00:08:15.820 --> 00:08:19.859
And. in the meantime.

187
00:08:23.360 --> 00:08:24.690
welcome aboard. son.

188
00:08:40.070 --> 00:08:41.070
Hey.

189
00:08:41.071 --> 00:08:42.359
Hey.

190
00:08:42.360 --> 00:08:44.069
How'd it go
with your dad?

191
00:08:44.070 --> 00:08:46.359
He was real excited
to have me on board.

192
00:08:46.360 --> 00:08:47.689
Ahem...

193
00:08:47.690 --> 00:08:49.609
which kind of sucked.
actually.

194
00:08:49.610 --> 00:08:51.069
Of course it did.

195
00:08:51.070 --> 00:08:53.019
I told you it would.

196
00:08:53.020 --> 00:08:55.859
Yeah. I hate
not telling him the truth.

197
00:08:55.860 --> 00:08:57.019
What'd you find out here?

198
00:08:57.020 --> 00:09:00.189
Absence of enzymes
in the digestive tract.

199
00:09:00.190 --> 00:09:01.150
Irregular ammonia levels.

200
00:09:01.151 --> 00:09:03.109
Death by starvation.

201
00:09:03.110 --> 00:09:05.320
What's up. party people?

202
00:09:06.980 --> 00:09:08.359
- I got dinner.
- Thanks. Jerry.

203
00:09:08.360 --> 00:09:10.070
- Thanks.
- Bone app-o-titty.

204
00:09:12.230 --> 00:09:13.899
Sushi? Really. Jer?

205
00:09:13.900 --> 00:09:15.319
Dealer's choice.

206
00:09:15.320 --> 00:09:16.860
I'm outta here. Tchk!

207
00:09:19.980 --> 00:09:22.110
All right.

208
00:09:24.900 --> 00:09:26.899
You know this isn't
what I was thinking

209
00:09:26.900 --> 00:09:30.149
when I said.
"Let's have dinner
like regular people"?

210
00:09:30.150 --> 00:09:31.979
No?

211
00:09:31.980 --> 00:09:33.359
Not exactly.

212
00:09:33.360 --> 00:09:37.649
All right.
How about we skip dinner

213
00:09:37.650 --> 00:09:39.940
and just get straight
to the clumsy sex part?

214
00:09:42.190 --> 00:09:44.520
Works for me.

215
00:09:50.190 --> 00:09:52.069
Yeah. I remember you.

216
00:09:59.900 --> 00:10:01.319
Hey.

217
00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:06.070
It's her tracker.

218
00:10:11.440 --> 00:10:13.229
She's coming back.

219
00:10:13.230 --> 00:10:14.979
She's coming back.

220
00:10:32.280 --> 00:10:33.690
Ben. over here.

221
00:10:39.230 --> 00:10:40.900
Maddie? Look at this.

222
00:10:45.320 --> 00:10:46.440
Think it's her sister?

223
00:10:47.520 --> 00:10:48.690
Maybe.

224
00:10:50.360 --> 00:10:52.279
Says she's off the beach.
She's in the woods.

225
00:10:52.280 --> 00:10:53.399
We're just
a little bit behind.

226
00:10:53.400 --> 00:10:55.019
You go.
I'll collect a sample.

227
00:10:55.020 --> 00:10:56.900
Okay.

228
00:11:06.190 --> 00:11:07.689
Yes. sir. as far
as he's concerned.

229
00:11:07.690 --> 00:11:09.939
she's just
a deranged nurse.

230
00:11:09.940 --> 00:11:12.019
So the fisherman's no longer
a threat to the project?

231
00:11:12.020 --> 00:11:13.819
If anything. he helped.

232
00:11:13.820 --> 00:11:16.359
He confirmed that she
disappeared at Libbey Beach.

233
00:11:16.360 --> 00:11:19.609
So we mapped
a logical trajectory
off the coast.

234
00:11:19.610 --> 00:11:23.229
We were able to isolate
sound patterns
100 miles offshore.

235
00:11:23.230 --> 00:11:25.939
They match recordings
from our specimen
in Bremerton.

236
00:11:25.940 --> 00:11:26.940
And you heard it?

237
00:11:26.941 --> 00:11:28.399
She's out there?

238
00:11:28.400 --> 00:11:30.480
Or others
very much like her.

239
00:11:32.730 --> 00:11:34.400
Better hope you found her.

240
00:12:07.440 --> 00:12:08.780
Stop!

241
00:12:10.570 --> 00:12:12.779
You follow.

242
00:12:12.780 --> 00:12:15.109
Water.

243
00:12:15.110 --> 00:12:17.189
You come back.

244
00:12:17.190 --> 00:12:19.109
You know their words.

245
00:12:19.110 --> 00:12:21.109
We need help...

246
00:12:21.110 --> 00:12:24.279
from the people.

247
00:12:24.280 --> 00:12:25.689
No!

248
00:12:25.690 --> 00:12:27.279
I know people hurt you.

249
00:12:27.280 --> 00:12:30.019
But some are good.

250
00:12:30.020 --> 00:12:31.150
Will help us.

251
00:12:45.440 --> 00:12:46.650
Come.

252
00:13:03.360 --> 00:13:05.190
Put it on.

253
00:13:10.860 --> 00:13:12.400
No!

254
00:13:14.860 --> 00:13:17.519
Wa... ter.

255
00:13:17.520 --> 00:13:20.019
I will stay.

256
00:13:20.020 --> 00:13:21.440
You go.

257
00:13:38.360 --> 00:13:40.730
We need the people.

258
00:13:46.610 --> 00:13:47.730
Now.

259
00:13:54.650 --> 00:13:55.730
Come in.

260
00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:58.900
I've got
the latest rendering.

261
00:14:00.520 --> 00:14:03.569
The engineer designed it
to your specifications. sir.

262
00:14:03.570 --> 00:14:05.109
As requested.
the system allows you to

263
00:14:05.110 --> 00:14:07.399
introduce a sedative
into the water.

264
00:14:09.110 --> 00:14:12.320
One touch will fully
immobilize a specimen.

265
00:14:13.480 --> 00:14:15.149
She told me to assure you

266
00:14:15.150 --> 00:14:16.820
there is no chance
of repeating Bremerton.

267
00:14:18.730 --> 00:14:20.360
Thank you. Nina.

268
00:14:36.900 --> 00:14:38.479
Any sign of them?

