00:28:43.650 --> 00:28:46.569
faster than we can
load it in the bins.

542
00:28:46.570 --> 00:28:48.399
Ben!

543
00:28:48.400 --> 00:28:50.479
Got a second?

544
00:28:50.480 --> 00:28:53.229
- Thanks. man.
- Sure.

545
00:28:53.230 --> 00:28:54.859
They found him
all the way in Alaska.

546
00:28:54.860 --> 00:28:56.649
- In Alaska. man.
- Crazy.

547
00:28:56.650 --> 00:28:59.569
And this Decker guy
told Chris what?

548
00:28:59.570 --> 00:29:01.479
That the psycho nurse
killed a bunch of people

549
00:29:01.480 --> 00:29:02.569
and he needed to find her.

550
00:29:02.570 --> 00:29:04.279
That doesn't make any sense.

551
00:29:04.280 --> 00:29:06.279
'Cause if she really was
this homicidal maniac.

552
00:29:06.280 --> 00:29:08.899
then the cops would have
been looking for Chris.

553
00:29:08.900 --> 00:29:10.319
not this Decker dude.

554
00:29:10.320 --> 00:29:12.319
some whacko fish doctor.

555
00:29:12.320 --> 00:29:14.519
Right. He's lying.

556
00:29:14.520 --> 00:29:15.939
Something happened
in that place.

557
00:29:15.940 --> 00:29:17.819
They wanted to find out
what Chris knew.

558
00:29:17.820 --> 00:29:20.399
Yeah. only he was
too drugged up
to know anything.

559
00:29:20.400 --> 00:29:22.819
so this Decker guy
just let him be.

560
00:29:22.820 --> 00:29:24.439
What'd you find out here?

561
00:29:24.440 --> 00:29:27.319
You ever heard of a company
called Coastal Mills?

562
00:29:27.320 --> 00:29:28.939
No. Why?

563
00:29:28.940 --> 00:29:31.359
They're the ones buying up
all that junk fish

564
00:29:31.360 --> 00:29:32.649
you guys
have been hauling in.

565
00:29:32.650 --> 00:29:34.899
I'm gonna try and figure out
who they are.

566
00:29:34.900 --> 00:29:37.319
So maybe
this Decker's connected.

567
00:29:37.320 --> 00:29:39.399
Well. let me know
what you find out.
I gotta go.

568
00:29:39.400 --> 00:29:41.650
Told the guys that
I would buy some pizza
to sop up the whisky.

569
00:29:49.860 --> 00:29:51.109
Thank you for coming.

570
00:29:51.110 --> 00:29:53.149
Well. thank you
for inviting me.

571
00:29:53.150 --> 00:29:54.319
Thanks.

572
00:29:54.320 --> 00:29:56.019
You have to try
Crab Louis salad.

573
00:29:56.020 --> 00:29:57.069
It's delicious.

574
00:29:57.070 --> 00:30:00.149
Thanks.

575
00:30:00.150 --> 00:30:02.069
So how's my boy
been lately?

576
00:30:02.070 --> 00:30:03.279
I never hear
from him anymore.

577
00:30:05.690 --> 00:30:08.149
I know the two of you
are busy with your work
at the Center.

578
00:30:08.150 --> 00:30:09.899
Yeah. we have been.

579
00:30:09.900 --> 00:30:12.109
We have this rescue
that's super demanding.

580
00:30:12.110 --> 00:30:13.859
It's eating up
a lot of Ben's time.

581
00:30:13.860 --> 00:30:15.399
He gets deep in it.
you know?

582
00:30:15.400 --> 00:30:16.859
I know.

583
00:30:16.860 --> 00:30:20.479
So how are you.
the two of you?

584
00:30:20.480 --> 00:30:21.689
We're fine.

585
00:30:21.690 --> 00:30:23.939
Great. actually.

586
00:30:23.940 --> 00:30:25.439
Good to hear.

587
00:30:25.440 --> 00:30:26.939
What did you rescue?

588
00:30:26.940 --> 00:30:30.520
A wounded seal pup.

589
00:30:35.020 --> 00:30:36.610
I know what's going on.

590
00:30:39.280 --> 00:30:43.319
I love my son.
but he has issues.

591
00:30:43.320 --> 00:30:46.439
Everybody has issues.

592
00:30:46.440 --> 00:30:48.439
Ben's a brilliant thinker.

593
00:30:48.440 --> 00:30:50.109
but he gets lost
in his own mind.

594
00:30:50.110 --> 00:30:52.109
and he...
he shuts people out.

595
00:30:52.110 --> 00:30:53.400
even his own mother.

596
00:30:54.940 --> 00:30:58.399
He does lose himself
in his work.

597
00:30:58.400 --> 00:31:01.019
All his little
wounded creatures.

598
00:31:01.020 --> 00:31:02.980
He's devoted to them.

599
00:31:04.360 --> 00:31:06.399
Are you
his current rescue?

600
00:31:06.400 --> 00:31:08.439
Excuse me?

601
00:31:08.440 --> 00:31:09.899
Don't take that
the wrong way.

602
00:31:09.900 --> 00:31:11.730
I was his first.

603
00:31:23.070 --> 00:31:24.729
What are you watching?

604
00:31:27.070 --> 00:31:29.859
Something stupid
with a monkey.

605
00:31:29.860 --> 00:31:31.569
What can I do you for.
handsome?

606
00:31:31.570 --> 00:31:32.859
Nothing. actually.

607
00:31:32.860 --> 00:31:35.569
I. brought you
a coffee.

608
00:31:35.570 --> 00:31:37.779
Still like it black
with a little bit of sugar?

609
00:31:37.780 --> 00:31:40.729
Since before
you could carry it.

610
00:31:40.730 --> 00:31:44.019
Hey. I was thinking
about taking my dad
out for lunch.

611
00:31:44.020 --> 00:31:45.229
Isn't that sweet.

612
00:31:45.230 --> 00:31:46.569
but he's already at lunch.

613
00:31:46.570 --> 00:31:49.979
with the buyer
from Schoenville Market?

614
00:31:49.980 --> 00:31:52.319
Mind if I wait here
till he gets back?

615
00:31:52.320 --> 00:31:54.109
Like you have to ask.

616
00:31:55.610 --> 00:31:57.479
Pownall Seafood.

617
00:31:57.480 --> 00:32:00.070
No. no.
He's not here right now.

618
00:32:04.520 --> 00:32:06.979
No. No.

619
00:32:06.980 --> 00:32:09.650
Thank you. Bye.

620
00:32:29.860 --> 00:32:31.979
What is it?

621
00:32:31.980 --> 00:32:33.940
Pownall Seafood.

622
00:32:44.730 --> 00:32:47.569
Yes. well. Tuesday.

623
00:32:47.570 --> 00:32:51.020
Tuesday would be wonderful.

624
00:33:00.280 --> 00:33:01.860
Yes. yes.

625
00:33:23.020 --> 00:33:25.019
He was consumed
with finding a cure

626
00:33:25.020 --> 00:33:28.479
or some miracle treatment
to get me back on my feet.

627
00:33:28.480 --> 00:33:30.149
He hated seeing you suffer.

628
00:33:30.150 --> 00:33:32.319
That's sort of what drives him.

629
00:33:32.320 --> 00:33:34.399
Yes. Thank you.

630
00:33:34.400 --> 00:33:37.399
He spent an entire year
online after my accident

631
00:33:37.400 --> 00:33:39.569
researching
spinal cord regeneration

632
00:33:39.570 --> 00:33:42.689
and calling clinics
around the world.

633
00:33:42.690 --> 00:33:43.819
He didn't sleep.

634
00:33:43.820 --> 00:33:46.069
Yeah.

635
00:33:46.070 --> 00:33:48.819
Not sleeping is a thing
with him sometimes.

636
00:33:48.820 --> 00:33:50.859
He fixates.

637
00:33:50.860 --> 00:33:53.860
While he's rescuing you.
you're... you're everything.

638
00:33:55.520 --> 00:33:57.689
I'm sure he helped you
get over your mother

639
00:33:57.690 --> 00:34:00.109
when you were
first together.

640
00:34:00.110 --> 00:34:02.649
But soon enough.
another wounded creature
comes along.

641
00:34:02.650 --> 00:34:04.980
and he dives
right in after her.

642
00:34:08.520 --> 00:34:10.480
Do you need
to get that. dear?

643
00:34:14.520 --> 00:34:16.899
Sorry. I... I kinda do.

644
00:34:16.900 --> 00:34:18.779
Another drink.
Ms. Pownall?

645
00:34:18.780 --> 00:34:21.649
Actually. Andrea.
I'll have the rosé
that I love.

646
00:34:21.650 --> 00:34:24.020
Thank you. Maddie?
Would you like something?

647
00:34:26.020 --> 00:34:28.149
Well. if it's Ben. please
tell him I said hello.

648
00:34:28.150 --> 00:34:32.519
I'm so sorry.
but I... I have to go.

649
00:34:32.520 --> 00:34:33.730
It's...

650
00:34:35.360 --> 00:34:37.569
A new rescue?

651
00:34:37.570 --> 00:34:39.729
It's the same rescue.
actually.

652
00:34:39.730 --> 00:34:41.779
because your son
doesn't give up on things.

653
00:34:41.780 --> 00:34:43.939
And by the way.

654
00:34:43.940 --> 00:34:45.569
I'm not a rescue.

655
00:34:45.570 --> 00:34:48.189
Okay.

656
00:34:48.190 --> 00:34:49.320
Well. thank you
for coming.

657
00:34:50.320 --> 00:34:52.110
Thanks for the salad.

658
00:34:58.110 --> 00:35:02.650
Actually. Andrea.
could you make that rosé
a martini. please?

659
00:35:07.230 --> 00:35:08.779
So this company.
Coastal Mills.

660
00:35:08.780 --> 00:35:10.229
reached out to my dad.

661
00:35:10.230 --> 00:35:11.479
offered to buy up
all the bycatch

662
00:35:11.480 --> 00:35:12.609
Pownall could deliver.

663
00:35:12.610 --> 00:35:14.779
And... and who runs
Coastal Mills?

664
00:35:14.780 --> 00:35:16.609
No one knows.
They don't exist online.

665
00:35:16.610 --> 00:35:19.149
No one at Pownall's
ever heard of them.

666
00:35:19.150 --> 00:35:22.279
There's no record
of what happens to the stuff
after they take it.

667
00:35:22.280 --> 00:35:24.609
It's like the trucks
just leave the fisheries

668
00:35:24.610 --> 00:35:27.229
and then disappear.

669
00:35:27.230 --> 00:35:30.279
And Xander said
the Department of Fish and Game

670
00:35:30.280 --> 00:35:32.359
stopped grounding
and fining boats

671
00:35:32.360 --> 00:35:34.189
for overfishing a month ago

672
00:35:34.190 --> 00:35:35.859
right around the same time.

673
00:35:35.860 --> 00:35:38.860
So the government's
letting it happen.

674
00:35:40.610 --> 00:35:42.520
They're making it happen.

675
00:35:44.440 --> 00:35:46.649
They're staving them out

676
00:35:46.650 --> 00:35:48.980
so they can catch
more of them.

677
00:36:40.110 --> 00:36:41.439
There you are.

678
00:36:42.780 --> 00:36:44.109
I've been looking
all over for you.

679
00:36:46.020 --> 00:36:49.359
I thought you might be
by the water.

680
00:36:49.360 --> 00:36:51.519
It's okay.

681
00:36:51.520 --> 00:36:54.020
I'm a friend.

682
00:36:57.440 --> 00:36:59.820
Thought
you might be hungry.

683
00:37:10.230 --> 00:37:11.569
It's okay.

684
00:37:11.570 --> 00:37:13.360
We want the same thing.

685
00:37:34.730 --> 00:37:38.689
Want to go back
to the water?

686
00:37:38.690 --> 00:37:40.190
But not without your sister?

687
00:37:43.730 --> 00:37:45.280
I can help.

688
00:37:49.980 --> 00:37:50.820
You?

689
00:37:53.110 --> 00:37:54.190
Yes.

690
00:37:55.730 --> 00:37:56.860
You can trust me. because...

691
00:38:00.820 --> 00:38:02.359
I am one of you.

692
00:38:11.360 --> 00:38:14.279
They want to hurt us?

693
00:38:14.280 --> 00:38:17.280
They want to catch you.

694
00:38:20.150 --> 00:38:22.690
Danger to go home.

695
00:38:24.070 --> 00:38:25.229
Yes.

696
00:38:29.480 --> 00:38:31.779
Not safe on land.

697
00:38:31.780 --> 00:38:33.940
Not safe in water.

698
00:38:35.570 --> 00:38:38.019
Nowhere is safe.

699
00:38:38.020 --> 00:38:40.819
We're gonna change that.

700
00:38:40.820 --> 00:38:44.189
We'll make it safe
for you

701
00:38:44.190 --> 00:38:46.020
to be wherever
you want to be.

702
00:38:47.780 --> 00:38:49.860
How?

703
00:38:52.230 --> 00:38:57.149
No. screw that. man. okay?

704
00:38:57.150 --> 00:39:01.019
None of this would have
ever happened if that...

705
00:39:01.020 --> 00:39:03.279
that freak fish hadn't
messed me up. you know?

706
00:39:03.280 --> 00:39:06.019
Did you ever ask
this Decker jerk

707
00:39:06.020 --> 00:39:08.229
what they did with the fish?

708
00:39:08.230 --> 00:39:10.859
They're studying it
or something.

709
00:39:10.860 --> 00:39:12.479
Who knows?

710
00:39:12.480 --> 00:39:16.859
Stop asking me
about it. okay?

711
00:39:16.860 --> 00:39:18.859
It's good to be home.

712
00:39:18.860 --> 00:39:20.900
Good to be home.

713
00:39:32.780 --> 00:39:34.779
Hey. it's Ben.
Leave me a message.

714
00:39:35.860 --> 00:39:39.069
Ben. dude...

715
00:39:39.070 --> 00:39:40.819
I'm just checkin' in.

716
00:39:40.820 --> 00:39:42.939
and wonderin'
what you found out.

717
00:39:42.940 --> 00:39:46.859
'cause...
'cause this Decker guy.

718
00:39:46.860 --> 00:39:50.899
I'm thinkin' he's the one.

719
00:39:50.900 --> 00:39:52.900
That he's behind it all.

720
00:39:58.980 --> 00:40:01.860
Ben. he ain't gonna
stop until he gets her back.
